        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 1:48PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Walsenburg, or 40 miles northwest of Trinidad, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Walsenburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
